   DRESDEN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
France and Germany agreed yesterday to maintain the present timetable for EC
economic and monetary union, Quentin Peel writes from Dresden.  Mr Klaus
Kinkel, the German foreign minister, and Mr Alain Juppe, his French
counterpart, said at a meeting in Dresden they would push for greater
economic convergence 'to revive the credibility of the aims of economic and
monetary union'.
