FT  25 AUG 93 / Consumer confidence in economy rises sharply
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Consumer confidence in the health of the economy has risen sharply,
according to the latest survey by Gallup.
Thirty-four per cent of respondents were optimistic about growth while 28
per cent were pessimistic. The positive balance of 6 per cent is 11 points
up on the previous month and stems from brighter expectations about jobs.
There is a growing belief that unemployment has stopped rising.
Low interest rates and a buoyant stock market also gave a further boost to
unit trust sales in July.
A net Pounds 948m flowed in and funds under management reached a record
Pounds 78.8bn, up from Pounds 76.3bn at the end of June.
