FT  24 AUG 93 / World News in Brief: Home Office says defecting Iraqi
diplomats can stay
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Two senior Iraqi diplomats who defected to the UK are to be allowed to stay
in the country the Home Office confirmed last night.
The Iraqi National Congress, an umbrella group for opponents of President
Saddam Hussein in the west, said the two - whom it described as long-serving
ambassadors - would announce at a news conference in London today that they
were joining the opposition movement.
